    One can also draw 2-arrows. (Internally, a 2-arrow is an object to which “${\Downarrow}” is appended.)
    \d-code(```
    \NCS.diagram(fun tb -> (
      let obj = tb#obj in
      let harr = tb#harr in
      let varr = tb#varr in
      let arr2 = tb#arr2 in
      [[obj {${A}}; harr {${f}} {}; obj {${B}}];
       [varr {} {${g}}; arr2 {${\alpha}}; varr {${h}} {}];
       [obj {${C}}; harr {} {${k}}; obj {${D}}]]));%
```);%
